    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT BEVEL\n\nBevel is the #1 AI Health Companion with over 1 million downloads globally. We help people make smarter decisions about their health every day by bringing together data across sleep, recovery, activity, nutrition, and more, and turning it into real-time, personalized guidance. Whether you're training for something big or just trying to feel better, Bevel helps you move with clarity and confidence.\n\nWe are a small, fast-moving team based in NYC, passionate about building beautiful and functional products. We are constantly looking for creative ways to push the capabilities of iOS/watchOS to create an app that is more intelligent, fun, and integrated into our users’ lives. \n\nBevel launched in early 2024, and we’ve been lucky to see incredible growth and support from our users. We’re looking to bring on a Senior iOS Engineer to help us build an ambitious roadmap https://feedback.bevel.health/. You’ll get an opportunity to shape the future of Bevel and have full ownership and creative freedom to create your life’s work.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES \n\n - Lead major features and architecture decisions across iOS and watchOS\n\n - Collaborate with design, product, and marketing to deliver world-class experiences\n\n - Build high-quality, maintainable code with strong attention to performance and detail\n\n - Push the limits of Apple’s frameworks — HealthKit, WatchKit, SwiftUI, etc.\n\n - Mentor other engineers, share best practices, and raise the engineering bar\n\n - Contribute to the evolution of Bevel’s app architecture and internal tools\n\n - Help define and refine our development process as we scale\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\n - 4+ years building native iOS apps with Swift and SwiftUI\n\n - Deep understanding of Apple’s frameworks, app lifecycle, and performance optimization\n\n - Experience shipping high-quality, design-centric consumer apps\n\n - Strong fundamentals in algorithms, data structures, and concurrency\n\n - A strong product mindset\n\n - Excellent communication and collaboration skills\n\n - A bias for action, ownership, and shipping\n\n - Excited about helping people live healthier, better lives\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Exciting work environment\n\n - Competitive salary \u0026 equity\n\n - Health, dental, and vision insurance\n\n - Commuter benefits\n\n - Paid lunch and dinner when in the office\n\n - Work-life balance\n\n - Pet-friendly office in Chelsea\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - 401k plan\n\n - Visa sponsorship if applicable\n\n⠀\n\nBevel celebrates and embraces diversity and is committed to building a team that represents a variety of experiences, backgrounds, and skills. We do not discriminate based on race, color, religion, marital status, age, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, non-disqualifying physical or mental disability, national origin, veteran status, or other applicable legally protected characteristics.",
